events.title: Alive & Well Productions - The Four Seasons of Hamadan (2025, San Fra (...) at Theater of Yugen @NOHSpace
events.description:
Event Name: The Four Seasons of Hamadan (San Francisco Premiere)  
Venue/Location: Theater of Yugen @ NOHSpace, San Francisco  
Date and Time: May 2, 2025, from 8:00 PM to 9:00 PM  
Tickets: $20 Early Bird, $25 Advance, $28 Door  
Event Description:  
Alive & Well Productions presents the San Francisco premiere of *The Four Seasons of Hamadan*, a duet blending Persian and Jewish music and dance traditions, composed by Kian Ravaei and choreographed by Annie Kahane. The performance features violinist Yvette Holzwarth and dancer Kate Myers, exploring intercultural harmony through folkloric forms reimagined in a contemporary style. Additionally, Helen Wicks performs _Radio Vision_, a solo piece inspired by Nadia Boulanger and early broadcast television history, accompanied by live cello and piano, incorporating circus-informed dance and personal research into Quincy Jones and Joe Gershenson.  
Registration link: [Event Tickets](https://dothebay.com/events/2025/5/2/alive-well-productions-the-four-seasons-of-hamadan-2025-san-francisco-premiere-with-helen-wicks-works-tickets)

events.title: Fort Mason Night Market, The Cowell Theater, San Francisco, CA | Sep 5, 2025
events.description:
**Event Name:** Fort Mason Night Market 2025

**Venue/Location:** The Cowell Theater at Pier 2, Fort Mason Center for Arts & Culture, 2 Marina Boulevard, San Francisco, CA 94123

**Date and Time:** September 5, 2025, from 5:00 PM to 10:00 PM

**Ticket/Registration URL:** [fortmason.org/event/fort-mason-night-market-2025/](https://fortmason.org/event/fort-mason-night-market-2025/)

**Event Description:**  
The Fort Mason Night Market 2025 is a monthly outdoor event launching on September 5, 2025, at the historic FMCAC campus. Following a successful inaugural event in December 2024, it features over 50 local artisans and craft vendors, more than 25 food and beverage options curated by Off the Grid, live music, DJs, creative workshops, public art installations, and seasonal offerings from local restaurants. The event is family-friendly, free to attend, and provides stunning waterfront views with seating at the “Secret Spot” Lounge. Additional activities include artmaking workshops for children and extended hours at local stores. Artisans interested in participating can contact West Coast Craft directly.

events.title: SF’s Chinatown “Autumn Moon Festival” (Sept. 27-28) + 2025 Grand Parade : Indybay
events.description:
Event Name: 35th Annual Autumn Moon Festival

Venue/Location: Chinatown, Grant Ave between California and Broadway, San Francisco

Date and Time: Saturday, September 27, 2025, from 11:00 am to 5:00 pm; main event kicks off with a grand parade at 11:00 am on September 27, 2025. The festival continues on September 28, 2025, from 11:00 am to 5:00 pm.

Full Description: The Autumn Moon Festival is a vibrant cultural celebration in San Francisco's Chinatown, featuring arts and crafts vendors, food stalls, live music, contemporary entertainment, mooncakes, lion dancing, and more. The event begins with a grand parade led by Mayor Daniel Lurie, cultural performers, and lion dancers, followed by lion dance and martial arts performances by the Yau Kung Moon Association. The 2025 theme celebrates the Monkey King (Sun Wukong), with special appearances by the mythical character and Shaolin acrobats, highlighting Chinese cultural heritage.

Note: No ticket, registration, Eventbrite, Meetup, or registration URLs are provided in the source.

events.description:
Event Name: San Francisco's Hello! Bachata/Salsa/Zouk/Kizomba Dance Festival (2025)

Venue/Location: Hyatt Regency SF Airport, 1333 Bayshore Highway, Burlingame, California (2.2 miles from San Francisco International Airport with complimentary shuttle)

Full Date and Time: July 25–27, 2025, starting on Friday, July 26 (time TBA) and ending on Monday, July 29 at 6:00 am (excluding pre-party)

Ticket/Registration URL: [https://hellobachatafestival.com/tickets](https://hellobachatafestival.com/tickets)

Event Description: A 3-day dance festival featuring up to 59 hours of workshops, day dancing, night parties, and competitions across Bachata, Salsa, Zouk, and Kizomba. The festival boasts an all-star lineup of international and regional instructors and headliners, including DJ Tronky (Bachata), Terry & Cecile (Salsa), Stephane Angles and DJ Sink (Kizomba). Special features include a Kizomba Jack and Jill competition with prizes, a heels workshop with Olga Vaskovskaia, and performances by renowned DJs and instructors from around the world. The event builds on monthly Bachata and Kizomba gatherings in San Francisco.

events.title: October Harvest Moon Sail on San Francisco Bay 2025
events.description:
Event Name: October Harvest Moon Sail on San Francisco Bay 2025

Venue/Location: Schooner Freda B, Sausalito Yacht Harbor, Slip 465, Sausalito, CA 94965

Date and Time: Tuesday, October 7, 2025, from 5:45 pm to 8:00 pm PDT (Boarding at 5:45 pm, Departure at 6:00 pm, Sunset at 6:45 pm, Moonrise at 6:57 pm)

Event Description: Experience a magical full moon cruise aboard the 80' gaff rigged schooner Schooner Freda B, offering scenic views of the San Francisco skyline, Golden Gate Bridge, Bay Bridge, Marin Headlands, Alcatraz, and Angel Islands. This event celebrates the October "Harvest Moon," the full moon closest to the Autumn Equinox, historically used by farmers for late-night harvests. events.title: PERSPECTIVES / SF:  The Artists of 1890 Bryant Street Studios
events.description:
Event Name: PERSPECTIVES / SF: The Artists of 1890 Bryant Street Studios  
Venue/Location: Sausalito Center For The Arts, 750 Bridgeway, Sausalito, United States  
Date & Time: Saturday, September 20, 2025, from 5:00 PM to 7:30 PM (GMT-07:00)  
Ticket/Registration URL: [Book tickets here](https://allevents.in/sausalito/perspectives-sf-the) (Tickets are suggested donation of $10, but entry is free)  
Event Description:  
PERSPECTIVES / SF showcases the diverse work of artists from 1890 Bryant Street Studios, a historic San Francisco artist collective located in the Inner Mission District. The event features a curated selection of paintings, sculptures, prints, photography, and mixed media by over 100 artists from this iconic space, which has a rich history dating back to its days as a mayonnaise factory. This exhibition marks the first time the community's work is displayed outside their studio, offering a unique glimpse into the vibrant Bay Area art scene. Attendees can enjoy lite bites and a no-host bar while exploring the creativity and legacy of this influential arts community.

events.title: Visual Arts
events.description:
**Event Name:** Visual Arts Panel Discussion: *Living in the Heart of Empire*  
**Venue/Location:** Cafe la Boheme, 3318 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110  
**Date and Time:** Thursday, May 8, 2025, 6:30 PM – 8:30 PM (120 mins with intermission)  
**Ticket/Registration URL:** [RSVP](https://www.sfiaf.org/20250508_2)  
**Event Description:** This free panel discussion features artists Francisco Franco, Max Martilla, Safi Kolozsvari Regalado, and Vida Kuang, moderated by Fernando Martí. The session explores how their artwork comments on, reflects, and voices immigrant diasporic communities amid the complexities of living within an empire. The event complements exhibitions like *In Diaspora* and *Tres Flores*, which showcase art reflecting immigrant experiences and themes of life, death, and meaning.

events.title: Startup Art Fair San Francisco at Hotel Del Sol
events.description:
Event Name: Startup Art Fair San Francisco

Venue/Location: Hotel Del Sol, 3100 Webster Street, San Francisco

Date and Time: April 18–20, 2025; Opening Night Party on April 18 from 7:00 PM to 10:00 PM

Ticket/Registration URL: [https://dothebay.com/events/2025/04/18/startup-art-fair-san-francisco-tickets](https://dothebay.com/events/2025/04/18/startup-art-fair-san-francisco-tickets)

Event Description: Startup Art Fair returns to San Francisco after a five-year hiatus, showcasing over 60 artists from across the country and California. The event transforms Hotel Del Sol into an immersive contemporary art experience featuring artwork, outdoor installations, sculptures, performances, panel discussions, and collaborations with local nonprofits. It emphasizes connecting emerging artists directly with art buyers, bypassing traditional galleries. The fair aims to highlight artists' vital role in culture and society during times of political and social complexity. The opening night includes music, food, and libations, and the event is aligned with the San Francisco Art Fair at Fort Mason.

Event Description: K Allado-McDowell presents a lecture on “On Neural Media,” exploring how generative AI and neural media influence culture, perception, and self-conception amidst global challenges like climate change. events.title: Enchanted Art and Other Ensorcellments (or, That AI Painting is Probably Cursed) - San Francisco Art Fair | April 2026

Event Name: Enchanted Art and Other Ensorcellments (or, That AI Painting is Probably Cursed) - San Francisco Art Fair | April 2026

Venue/Location: Art Market San Francisco Theater

Date & Time: Saturday, April 22, 2023, 5:30 PM – 6:30 PM

Event Description: Presented by Aaron Gach of the Center for Tactical Magic, this interactive event explores the magical qualities of contemporary art—its ability to enchant, invoke, or mislead. Gach will examine recent trends in art that perform various forms of magic, drawing on his collaborations with diverse professionals such as magicians, scientists, activists, and more. The talk aims to illuminate the creative inquiries behind modern art and differentiate between genuine artistic enchantment and deception. The Center for Tactical Magic, founded in 2000, is known for projects integrating art, magic, and tactics to promote social change, with exhibitions at major institutions worldwide.

Note: No ticket, registration, Eventbrite, Meetup, or specific registration links are provided on the webpage.

events.title: Solarpunkification: Art & Systems Change Exhibition
events.description:
**Event Name:** Solarpunkification: Art & Systems Change Exhibition

**Venue/Location:** Live Worms Gallery, 1345 Grant Ave, North Beach, San Francisco, CA 94133

**Date and Time:** Friday, February 7, 2025, from 5:00 PM to 10:00 PM

**Ticket/Registration URL:** [Event Details & Registration](https://impact-investing-for-systemic-change.ticketleap.com/solarpunkification/dates/Feb-07-2025_at_0500PM)

**Event Description:** This event explores themes of sustainable futures through art and systems change. It features an opening talk by Bobby Fishkin on "Working Backwards from a Solar Punk Future," a special guest appearance by solar punk fiction author Sheridan Tatsuno, a psychedelic hip hop performance by Brotha Peace, and a panel discussion addressing intergenerational trauma, art, plant-based healing, and community building. The event concludes with an audience Q&A and reasoning circle, fostering dialogue on positive systemic transformation. The event is free to attend.

events.title: Jonathon Keats: The Future Democracies Laboratory at MODERNISM INC.
events.description:
Event Name: The Future Democracies Laboratory: Political Innovations by Jonathon Keats

Venue/Location: Modernism Gallery, San Francisco, California

Date and Time: October 30, 2024 (One-night only showroom experience)

Ticket/Registration URL: Not provided on the webpage

Event Description: Modernism presents a one-night showroom experience showcasing the Future Democracies Laboratory created by Jonathon Keats at San Jose State University. The laboratory develops innovative technologies aimed at transforming democracy and governance, especially amid crises in American democracy and global ecology. Key innovations include protocols for including all living beings in political processes and experiments with re-engineering electoral systems—such as replacing politicians with weighted random number generators that emulate legislative processes. The event offers the public a chance to interact with these speculative technologies, fostering collective engagement and rethinking traditional political dogma. Presented by MODERNISM INC., the event is free to attend.

Attendees are encouraged to wear costumes reflecting Gothic, Victorian, or spooky styles (costumes optional). Children aged 10 and older require tickets. events.title: Book Lecture at UC Berkeley: How Local Organizations Shape US Education
events.description:
Event Name: Book Lecture at UC Berkeley: How Local Organizations Shape US Education  
Venue/Location: UC Berkeley, Berkeley Way West Building, 2121 Berkeley Way, Berkeley, CA  
Date and Time: Wednesday, April 30, 2025, from 4:30 pm to 6:00 pm  
Registration URL: RSVP requested at [bit.ly/subtlewebslaunch](https://bit.ly/subtlewebslaunch)  
Event Description: This lecture, led by UC Berkeley's Assistant Professor Jose Eos Trinidad, explores how local organizations outside schools influence and shape US education systems. Using examples like school dropout prediction systems in Chicago, Philadelphia, and NYC, the talk reveals how decentralized changes occur through "outside-in" initiatives of networked organizations rather than traditional top-down or bottom-up processes. A panel discussion featuring Gloria Lee of Educate78 and Oakland REACH, and Karling Aguilera-Fort, deputy superintendent of San Francisco USD, will follow. The event is free with RSVP required.

- Saturday: 10:00 am – 6:30 pm  
- Sunday: 8:00 am – 4:30 pm

Registration URL: [Get Tickets](https://barbellrehab.com/san-francisco/#tickets)

This is a 2-day live certification focused on coaching and modifying barbell lifts for clients with pain or mobility limitations. The course teaches a step-by-step approach to safely and effectively adjust lifts like squats, deadlifts, bench presses, and overhead presses, emphasizing pain management and individualized modifications. **Ticket/Registration URL:** [https://dothebay.com/events/2025/2/2/irl-movie-clu](https://dothebay.com/events/2025/2/2/irl-movie-clu)

**Event Description:**  
Join the IRL Movie Club for a screening of *The Thinking Game*, a documentary that explores DeepMind’s pursuit of artificial general intelligence (AGI). Filmed over five years, it highlights breakthroughs like AlphaFold, which solved a 50-year biology challenge, and showcases the intense efforts, setbacks, and triumphs of AI research led by Demis Hassabis. The film offers insight into one of the most significant scientific endeavors of our time, emphasizing the potential impact of AGI on our future. The event is an in-person gathering designed for community connection and discussion around trending topics in science and technology.

events.title: Solarpunkification Opening Weekend | Plura
events.description:
Event Name: Solarpunkification Opening Weekend

Venue/Location: Live Worms Gallery, 1345 Grant Avenue, North Beach, San Francisco, CA

Full Date and Time:
- Friday, February 7, 2025, 5:00 PM – 10:00 PM
- Saturday, February 8, 2025, 2:00 PM – 7:00 PM
- Sunday, February 9, 2025, 2:00 PM – 7:00 PM

Ticket/Registration URL: [https://www.solarpunkification.art/](https://www.solarpunkification.art/)

Event Description: The Solarpunkification Opening Weekend is an immersive art and systems change exhibition held at Live Worms Gallery in San Francisco's North Beach. The event features a series of talks, panels, workshops, and performances exploring solarpunk themes—focusing on the harmonious integration of regenerative technology and nature. Highlights include discussions on future visions, community resilience, wildfire risk reduction, and collective narratives, alongside performances by artists like Brotha Peace and Sheridan Tatsuno. Attendees can engage with print-on-demand artwork and participate in a vibrant community gathering dedicated to envisioning sustainable, regenerative futures.

events.title: The Philosophy and Psychology of Anger
events.description:
Event Name: The Philosophy and Psychology of Anger  
Venue/Location: Online (no physical venue)  
Date and Time: Saturday, March 22, 9:00 am – 1:30 pm PDT  
Registration URL: [https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/the-philosophy-and-psy](https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/the-philosophy-and-psy)  
Event Description:  
Join a 4.5-hour online event exploring the roots of anger through philosophy and psychology. The program features lectures and discussions with experts on topics such as Seneca’s and Marcus Aurelius’s perspectives on anger, Aristotelian approaches, ancient mythology, and modern therapeutic methods including CBT, REBT, ACT, and schema therapy. Speakers include philosophers, psychologists, and mental health professionals, offering insights into understanding, managing, and overcoming anger from ancient and contemporary viewpoints.

events.title: What is Intelligence? at Cowell Theater in San Francisco - September 16, 2025 | SF Station
events.description:
Event Name: What is Intelligence?  
Venue/Location: Cowell Theater, Fort Mason Center, San Francisco, CA 94123  
Date and Time: September 16, 2025, at 7:00 PM  
Ticket/Registration URL: [Buy Tickets](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/what-is-intelligence-tickets-1302700214409)  
Event Description: Blaise Agüera y Arcas, CTO at Google, explores the nature of intelligence and how AI's development aligns with evolution. Drawing on decades of theory, literature, and artificial life experiments, he argues that some modern AI systems possess claims to intelligence, consciousness, and free will. The event is part of a larger project including a printed book and experimental formats challenging traditional academic publishing, and is presented by Antikythera and MIT Press. Attendees can also mingle over drinks and small bites before and after the talk.

events.title: Annual meeting of INEBRIA in San Francisco
events.description:
**Event Name:** Annual Meeting of INEBRIA

**Venue/Location:** University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) and Kaiser Permanente Division of Research, San Francisco

**Full Date and Time:** September 24-26, 2025

**Event Description:**  
The INEBRIA annual meeting focuses on global leadership in developing, evaluating, and implementing evidence-based practices for early identification and brief interventions for hazardous and harmful substance use. The conference covers research on screening and brief interventions (SBI), including innovative outreach methods and delivery outside traditional healthcare settings. Special emphasis is placed on SBI in low- and middle-income countries and low-resource settings in high-income countries. Dr. William Miller will deliver the keynote Nick Heather lecture.

events.title: Seminars
events.description:
Event Name: Seminars

Venue/Location: Room 619, Sino Building, CUHK

Date and Time: April 8th, 2025, Tuesday, 11:00 am – 12:00 pm

Registration URL: [Zoom Link](https://cuhk.zoom.us/j/97765140597)

Event Description: The seminar titled "Lingering episodic memory modes reflect adaptations to autocorrelation in the natural environment" features Dr. Qihong Lu from Columbia University. It explores how humans prioritize episodic retrieval versus encoding, highlighting how memory modes adapt to environmental autocorrelation. Using neural network models and empirical studies, the talk demonstrates that memory modes are influenced by the structure of natural experiences, with stronger autocorrelation leading to more pronounced memory mode effects. The session includes a replay link valid until April 22, 2025.

events.title: AI Workshop (SF): Self-hosted LLMs Agent and Build Scalable Workflows for LLMs
events.description:
Event Name: AI Workshop (SF): Self-hosted LLMs Agent and Build Scalable Workflows for LLMs

Venue/Location: Microsoft SF, 555 California Street, Suite 200, San Francisco, CA 94104

Date and Time: May 15, 2024, at 05:00 PM PDT

Registration URL: No specific Eventbrite, Meetup, or registration link provided; attendees must register via the event page and will receive a QR code from Microsoft for building access. The registration process involves providing first name, last name, and email, with privacy details outlined on the Microsoft privacy statement.

Event Description: This in-person workshop in San Francisco offers hands-on sessions focused on AI, Generative AI, LLMs, and machine learning. It features two main workshops: one on building self-hosted LLM agents using open-source tools like WasmEdge and Rust, enabling participants to run personal AI agents on their laptops or edge devices; and another on constructing scalable workflows for LLMs with tools such as Union.ai, Hugging Face, and Weights & Biases, covering model fine-tuning, workflow orchestration, and experiment management. The event includes networking, food, drinks, and opportunities to engage with speakers and fellow developers.

**Registration URL:** [https://ai.bythebay.io/register](https://ai.bythebay.io/register)

AI By The Bay is a comprehensive conference focusing on advanced AI topics such as model quantization, hardware acceleration, efficient serving architectures, and self-improving pipelines. The event features four main tracks: Thoughtful Software, Engineering & Infrastructure, Distributed Data, and Open Source, covering the latest developments in AI software, systems, data management, and open-source tools. The conference is ideal for professionals in engineering, computer science, and technology sectors interested in cutting-edge AI research and practical implementation.

events.title: SF AI, Machine Learning and Data Science Meetup | Meetup
events.description:
Event Name: Visual Agents Workshop Part 3: Teaching Machines to See and Click

Venue/Location: Virtual (online via Zoom)

Date and Time: August 29, 2025, at 9:00 AM Pacific Time

Registration URL: [Register for the Zoom](https://voxel51.com/events/from-research-to-reality-building-gui-agents-that-actually-work-august-29-2025)

Event Description: This is the final part of a three-session virtual workshop series focused on visual agents and GUI interactions. It covers fine-tuning foundation vision-language models (like Qwen2.5-VL) into GUI specialists capable of navigating interfaces with human-like precision. Participants will learn modern fine-tuning strategies, develop training pipelines for diverse datasets, evaluate models for GUI automation, and deploy models in real-world testing environments. The session is led by Harpreet Sahota, a machine learning engineer with expertise in deep learning, generative AI, and multimodal AI.

events.title: AI Day SF | Internet Society – San Francisco Bay Area Chapter
events.description:
Event Name: AI Day SF

Venue/Location: Google Community Space, 188 Embarcadero, San Francisco

Date and Time: February 6, 2025, from 9:00 am to 9:00 pm (food provided)

Registration URL: [https://aidaysf.org](https://aidaysf.org)

Event Description:  
AI Day SF is a full-day event co-hosted by the Internet Society and the Association for Computing Machinery, focusing on the current impact of AI across various sectors of society. The event features multiple sessions, including AI tooling training and thought leadership discussions, aimed at enhancing understanding of AI's role today. It serves as a platform for learning, networking, and exploring how AI influences legal, regulatory, and societal domains. The event is also a fundraising initiative, with tax-deductible contributions supporting future activities.

events.description:
Event Name: What is Intelligence?  
Venue/Location: Cowell Theater, Fort Mason Center, San Francisco, CA  
Date and Time: September 16, 2025, at 7:00 PM  
Ticket/Registration URL: [Buy Tickets](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/what-is-intelligence-tickets-1302700214409)  
Event Description: Blaise Agüera y Arcas, VP, Fellow and CTO of Technology & Society at Google, explores the nature of intelligence and how AI's development is a natural evolution. Date and Time: Tuesday, May 13, 7:00 PM – 8:30 PM PDT  
Ticket/Registration URL: [Eventbrite link](https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ask-a-science-envoy-a)  
Event Description: This interactive event features early-career scientists from Wonderfest presenting on provocative topics. The event is free, unticketed, and includes Q&A sessions, held at HopMonk Tavern Novato.

events.title: Exploring the Gravitational Wave Universe: New Discoveries + LIGO Astronomy
events.description:
Event Name: Exploring the Gravitational Wave Universe: New Discoveries + LIGO Astronomy

Venue/Location: 199 Museum Way, San Francisco, CA

Date and Time: Wednesday night, July 15, 2025 (exact time not specified)

Ticket/Registration URL: No specific registration link provided; the event is free and open to the public.

Event Description: The San Francisco Amateur Astronomers are hosting a free lecture presented by Prof. Brian Lantz, a Stanford University researcher specializing in gravitational wave detection. The talk will cover the revolutionary field of gravitational wave astronomy, including the history of LIGO’s first detection in 2015, recent discoveries of nearly 300 signals, and insights gained from black hole and neutron star mergers. Prof. Lantz will discuss how gravitational waves are measured—despite their minuscule effect—and explore future developments in this emerging field. The event provides an opportunity to learn about the science behind detecting ripples in space caused by cosmic collisions.

**Registration/Ticket URL:** [Register here](https://www.bayareascience.org/calendar/link/index.php?tID=1&oID=33834)

events.title: SETI Live: Automated Discovery of Anomalous Features
events.description:
**Event Name:** SETI Live: Automated Discovery of Anomalous Features  
**Venue/Location:** SETI Institute, California  
**Date and Time:** Thursday, January 30, 2025, 09:00 AM – 09:30 AM  
**Registration URL:** [Click here to register](https://www.bayareascience.org/calendar/link/index.php?tID=1&oID=37458)  
**Event Description:**  
Join senior planetary astronomer Franck Marchis and authors Adam Lesnikowski and Daniel Angerhausen for a discussion on a groundbreaking automated system developed by scientists to identify unusual features in planetary imagery, specifically from NASA's Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter. This system acts as the first anomaly detector for planetary images, efficiently highlighting significant geological formations, human landings, or spacecraft crashes within vast data archives. The event explores how this innovative approach advances planetary science by uncovering hidden insights and its potential applications across various scientific fields. The event is free and available to attend online via Facebook or YouTube.

events.title: Measuring the Effect of Gravity on Antimatter
events.description:
**Event Name:** Measuring the Effect of Gravity on Antimatter  
**Venue/Location:** UC Berkeley, Room 1, Berkeley, CA 94720  
**Date and Time:** Monday, March 4, 2024, 4:15 PM – 5:15 PM  
**Event Description:** This lecture discusses recent experiments by CERN’s ALPHA collaboration measuring how antimatter, specifically antihydrogen atoms, responds to gravity. The experiments, which are the first direct free-fall measurements, show antimatter falls downward with an acceleration close to standard gravity (g=9.8 m/s²), strongly ruling out the possibility of antimatter falling upwards. The talk reviews the historical context, current experimental efforts, and details of how the measurement was conducted using a magnetic balance.  
**Registration/Tickets:** Free event. No specific registration link provided.  
**Additional Links:** [Event webpage](https://www.bayareascience.org/calendar/index.php?eID=35146)

events.description:
**Event Name:** SynBioBeta 2024: The Global Synthetic Biology Conference - Innovation Discovery

**Venue/Location:** San Jose McEnery Convention Center, 150 W San Carlos St, San Jose, CA 95113

**Date and Time:** All day on Thursday, May 9, 2024, with other dates available (specific schedule for other days not provided)

**Event Description:**  
A four-day summit focused on synthetic biology advancements. The conference explores the decreasing costs and increasing accessibility of DNA reading, writing, and editing technologies. Highlights include breakthroughs in medical fields such as cell therapies, vaccines, and living medicines, as well as industrial applications like bio-based jet fuels, textiles, concrete, and chemicals. Attendees will engage with entrepreneurs developing innovative foods, crops, and fragrances, and examine how these technologies can promote sustainable manufacturing ecosystems.

events.title: Human Hibernation? – Jan 9 – Wonderfest – Bay Area Beacon of Science
events.description:
Event Name: Human Hibernation? – Jan 9  
Venue/Location: HopMonk Tavern, 224 Vintage Way, Novato, CA 94945  
Date and Time: January 9, 2024, at 7:00 PM (Tuesday), approximately 1.5 hours duration  
Ticket/Registration URL: The event is free and unticketed; donations can be made via the Eventbrite window on the page (specific link not provided).  
Event Description: This lecture features Dr. Art Wallace, Professor and Vice-Chair of Anesthesiology at UCSF, discussing the potential of anesthesia and hibernation in enabling long-duration human spaceflight. The talk explores scientific advances, challenges—such as the detrimental effects of anesthesia and the fact that many animals do not revive from hibernation—and the possibility of future medical breakthroughs for deep-space travel. The event is held at HopMonk Tavern in Novato, CA, on January 9, 2024, at 7 PM, and is free to attend with an option for donations via Eventbrite.
